This Privacy Policy outlines how Frenzone.Live, a social media platform, collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal information.

1. Information We Collect

We collect the following information to operate Frenzone.Live and provide you with a safe and enjoyable experience:

Account Information: Your name, username, email address, and a secure password you create.
User-Generated Content: Videos, images, comments, and other content you upload or share on Frenzone.Live. This may include profile pictures, posts, reels, live stream information, and messages.
Usage Information: Data about how you interact with Frenzone.Live, such as your searches, likes, comments, follows, and views. This also includes information about your device and browsing activity on the platform.
2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information for the following purposes:

To provide you with Frenzone.Live services: This includes creating your account, allowing you to post and interact with content, and personalize your experience.
To improve and personalize Frenzone.Live: We analyze usage data to understand user trends and preferences, which helps us improve features and content recommendations.
To communicate with you: We may send you email notifications about your account activity, platform updates, and promotional offers (with your consent).
To ensure safety and security: We use your information to prevent fraud, abuse, and other harmful activities on the platform.
To comply with legal obligations: We may need to use or disclose your information to comply with laws, regulations, or legal proceedings.
3. Your Privacy Choices

You have control over your information on Frenzone.Live:

Account Settings: You can access and update your profile information, email address, and password at any time.
Privacy Settings: You can control who can see your posts, profile information, and activity.
Content Management: You can delete or edit your posts, reels, and other content you've shared.
Cookie Preferences: You can manage cookies through your browser settings to control how Frenzone.Live uses cookies for tracking and personalization.
Communication Preferences: You can opt out of receiving promotional emails by following the unsubscribe instructions in the emails.
4. Data Security

We take data security seriously and implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information. This includes secure storage practices, regular security audits, and access controls.

5. Children's Privacy

Frenzone.Live is for users aged 13 and above. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us at info@frenzone.live for immediate deletion.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes by email or a prominent notice on the platform.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at info@frenzone.live.

